				<!-- start pageDataHeading -->
				<h1>Aged Care Entry Record (ACER) form 065-13060050</h1>
<ul id="tabs-primary"><li><a class="active students" href="../older-australians/065-13060050-01.html">Background</a></li><li><a href="../older-australians/065-13060050-03.html">Process</a></li><li><a href="../older-australians/065-13060050-04.html">References</a></li><li><a href="../older-australians/065-13060050-05.html">Resources</a></li></ul>
				<!-- end pageDataHeading -->
				
				<!-- start pageDataContent -->
				<div id="bgtab" class="">
					
<div id="relatedMessagesDiv"></div>


					<div class="unitRight"><a href="javascript:expandCollapseSections()" id="toggleText" alt="Expand/Collapse all sections" title="Expand/Collapse all sections"><img src="../../supportingContent/images/icons/toggle_plus.gif"align="top" id="toggleImage"border="0" alt="Expand/Collapse all sections"width="16" height="16">Expand all</a></div><br><br>

					<body>
<a name="top" class="anchor"></a><div id="contentObp" class="main"><div id="topnav"></div>


<p>This document outlines information about the Aged Care Entry Record (ACER) form. </p>

<p></p>
<div class="twisty">
	
<a class="anchor" name="bp01_L2GT_Historical_SPAR"></a>
<h2 id="_Toc344898764">Historical SPARC process</h2>

	<div class="collapsible_container">
		<div class="block">

<p>The System for the Payment of Aged Residential Care (SPARC) is the legacy aged care payment system for residential care. SPARC is a view only system from 20 August 2022.</p>

<p>To view the legacy SPARC process, see the <a target="_blank" href="../older-australians/065-13060050-01.html?PageVersion=11776">historical version</a>.</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>


<p></p>
<div class="twisty">
	
<a class="anchor" name="bp01_L2GT_ACER_form"></a>
<h2 id="_Toc344898764">ACER form</h2>

	<div class="collapsible_container">
		<div class="block">

<p>Aged care services use the ACER form to notify Services Australia of new care recipients entering permanent residential care or home care. </p>

<p>Services Australia use the ACER form to match the care recipient with either Centrelink or the Department of Veterans' Affairs (DVA) records for means testing purposes.</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>


<p></p>
<div class="twisty">
	
<a class="anchor" name="bp01_L2GT_Award_or_settle"></a>
<h2 id="bp01_L2GT_Award_or_settle">Award or settlement indicator on the ACER form</h2>

	<div class="collapsible_container">
		<div class="block">

<p>Aged care services&#58;</p>
		<ul>		<li>
must inform the Department of Health and Aged Care when a care recipient has&#58;</li>
			<ul>			<li>
entered residential care, and/or </li>
			<li>
commences a Home Care Package, with</li>
			<li>
a compensation entitlement such as an entitlement to compensation arising from a workplace, motor vehicle accident or from a common law claim</li>		</ul>
		<li>
can do this by completing the relevant section on the ACER form lodged with Services Australia</li>
			<ul>			<li>
the agency will advice the Department of Health and Aged Care</li>
			</ul>			</ul>
<p>The Department of Health and Aged Care&#58; </p>
		<ul>		<li>
will assess the compensation details</li>
		<li>
may then apply a compensation payment reduction from the care recipient’s entry date</li>
		<li>
advise the aged care service and the compensable care recipient of the amount of the compensation payment reduction</li>
			<ul>			<li>
the aged care service will be able to invoice the compensable care recipient for the total amount of the compensation payment reduction in addition to the other relevant fees and charges</li>
			</ul>			</ul>
<p>The Department of Health and Aged Care will recover the aged care services subsidy payments made on behalf of the care recipient, for the period where compensation payment reduction should have applied if&#58;</p>
		<ul>		<li>
aged care services does not inform that a care recipient is entitled to compensation; and</li>
		<li>
the information is made at a later date</li>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>
		</ul>

<p></p>
<div class="twisty">
	
<a class="anchor" name="bp01_L2GT_Residential_Car01"></a>
<h2 id="bp01_L2GT_Residential_Car01">Residential Care subsidies (pre-entry leave)</h2>

	<div class="collapsible_container">
		<div class="block">

<p>Previously a subsidy was paid for up to 7 days before a care recipient entered residential care if an approved provider was holding a place for the care recipient. This was known as pre-entry leave. The payment of residential care subsidies and supplements for the period of pre-entry leave ceased from 1 July 2015 and this subsidy was removed altogether. This means that the government no longer subsidised periods of pre-entry leave. A subsidy will only begin to be paid once the care recipient has actually entered care.</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>


<p></p>

<p>The <a href="../older-australians/065-13060050-05.html">Resources</a> page contains </p>		<ul>		<li>

frequency asked questions</li>		<li>

contact details</li>		<li>

a link to the ACER form</li>		<li>

links to the Department of Health and Aged Care website</li>		</ul>

<p></p>
